    null,
    null,
    E'A KPI card (or BAN — Big-Ass Number) is the simplest viz: one number, one label, optionally one trend indicator. They dominate dashboards because executives scan, not read. The trap is putting too many KPIs on one screen — past 8-10, attention scatters. Pair each KPI with a sparkline or a small comparison (''vs target'', ''vs last month''). And size matters: the headline number should be 3-5x the label size, otherwise the eye doesn''t know what to focus on.',
