    null,
    E'Gantt charts show duration: each row is a task or entity, each bar spans start → end. They scale to hundreds of rows if you give the user filters. Use them for project plans (the original use case), but also for any ''event with duration'' data — server uptime windows, employee tenure, contract terms. The classic mistake is putting Gantt in a dashboard with no filtering — anyone with 100+ items will scroll past. Add a date range filter and category facets, always.',
