    null,
    null,
    E'Pie charts are decoded by angle, and humans are bad at angles. The chart-shaming brigade is right about most pies — a horizontal bar chart conveys the same data more accurately. That said, pies do work for two specific cases: (1) part-to-whole at a glance when there are 2-3 categories and the proportions are dramatic (40/30/30 reads fine), or (2) communicating proportion to a non-analytical audience that intuits pies. For everything else, use a bar.',
